The above paper is written cryptically but the topic is relevant. The techniques haven't been described properly. I couldn't learn anything


http://www.cs.bu.edu/techreports/pdf/1996-006-measuring-bottleneck-link.pdf
Bandwidth estimation with only ICMP packets. This is the ideal tool. The problem is, its not available for Linux

http://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/ip/simple-network-management-protocol-snmp/8141-calculate-bandwidth-snmp.html
Bandwidth utilization for one interface using SNMP only. Ignores rate limiting. Only compares to line rate of the interface
